-- Hungary’s Varga May Succeed Simor as Central Bank Head, Nol Says
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-05-15T13:46:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/hungary-s-varga-may-succeed-simor-as-central-bank-head-nol-says.html
Mihaly Varga, Hungary’s recently
appointed chief negotiator with the  International Monetary Fund 
and the European Union may succeed Andras Simor as president of
the central bank when Simor’s term ends in March, news  Website 
Nol said, citing an unidentified government official.  Varga may be slated to become finance minister should Prime
Minister Viktor Orban decide to set up an independent Finance
Ministry, which is “doubtful,” Nol cited the official as
saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
